Renaissance Research AI – Engineering Delivery Package
Executive Summary
Renaissance Research AI is an academic research platform designed for graduate students, art historians, and museum researchers studying 15th century Italian Renaissance paintings. The platform combines AI-assisted research, semantic artwork search, manuscript analysis, citation management, image analysis, multilingual archival translation, and collaborative annotation tools.
Core User Personas
Graduate Students, Art History Professors, and Museum Researchers who require AI-assisted scholarly workflows, annotation systems, archival search, and semantic analysis.
Core Features
- AI Research Assistant
- Semantic Painting Search
- Manuscript & Archive Analysis
- Visual Similarity Search
- Citation Generator
- Collaborative Annotation Workspace
Recommended Technology Stack
Frontend: Next.js, TypeScript, TailwindCSS
Backend: FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Redis
AI Stack: OpenAI GPT-4o, Embeddings API, LangGraph, Pinecone, OCR Pipeline
AI Workflow
User Uploads Source → OCR/Text Extraction → Chunking Pipeline → Embedding Generation → Vector Database → Semantic Search + AI Responses
Reviewer Findings
Strengths: Strong academic specialization, scalable semantic architecture.
Risks: OCR costs, hallucination risk, image storage scaling.
Recommendations: Source grounding, async processing, CDN optimization.
Example Database Schema
CREATE TABLE research_documents (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    title TEXT,
    author TEXT,
    publication_year INT,
    summary TEXT,
    embedding VECTOR(1536),
    uploaded_by UUID
);
CREATE TABLE paintings (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    title TEXT,
    artist TEXT,
    year_created INT,
    region TEXT,
    medium TEXT,
    image_url TEXT,
    embedding VECTOR(1536)
);
CREATE TABLE annotations (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    painting_id UUID,
    user_id UUID,
    annotation TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);
